      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEE HEZA SPORT NZ (8) drew on the back row and worked before digging deep to go under narrowly in the Narrogin Cup last start. Came from a similar barrier to this when kicking off his campaign with a third to topliner Minstrel at this circuit and distance three back. Race fit so can break through. YOURE SO FINE NZ (9) did a great job last week when he made a winning return after four months, drawing on the back row and racing three wide without cover before digging deep to get home by a head at this circuit and distance last week. Draws wide but races well second-up so should be improve. MENEMSHA (12) may need a touch of luck from a back row draw but has been racing well at this circuit and distance, winning two back then racing wide and working but fighting well to miss Youre So Fine by a head last week. MAXIMUM ROCK (11) is another that draws on the back line but he too is going well with a win and a placing in his last two outings.",
